rgely forgotten today is one of Mumford’s key insights—that Melville’s darkness was balanced by an inspiring determination to endure.Amid today’s foreboding over global warming, racism, technology, pandemics, and other crises, Melville and Mumford remind us that we’ve been in this struggle for a long time. To rediscover these writers today is to rediscover how history can offer hope in dark times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 0aCriticszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aA. Mitchell Palmer.  aAhab.  aAmericans.  aAt the Core.  aAwareness.  aBarbarian.  aBilly Budd.  aBiography.  aCaptain Ahab.  aCareer.  aClarel.  aCommodity.  aConsciousness.  aDeep history.  aDetermination.  aDisenchantment.  aE. M. Forster.  aEmblem.  aEscapism.  aEssay.  aEthos.  aExploration.  aGeorge Perkins Marsh.  aGilded Age.  aHerman Melville.  aImpressment.  aIn This World.  aJohn Claggart.  aKitimat.  aLangston Hughes.  aLewis Mumford.  aMalcolm Cowley.  aManifest destiny.  aMechanization.  aMemoir.  aMichael Shelden.  aMoby-Dick.  aModernity.  aMr.  aNarrative.  aNathaniel Hawthorne.  aNear East.  aOahu.  aOmoo.  aOrganism.  aPoetry.  aPuritans.  aQueequeg.  aRedburn.  aReign.  aRequirement.  aRole.  aRomanticism.  aScientism.  aScurvy.  aSlavery.  aSuffering.  aTechnology.  aThe Conduct of Life.  aThe Encantadas.  aThe Other Hand.  aThe Philosopher.  aThe Rest of the Story.  aThe Spirit of the Age.  aTypee.  aUncertainty.  aUtopia.  aV.  aWorks and Days.  aWriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBO